## 2. Canonical Telemetry Schema
The global state matrix tracks three distinct operational arcs (Semantic, Physical, and Cognitive). All messages passing over the inter-manifold wire protocol must conform to this schema layout.
### 2.1 Schema Definition (combined_manifold.proto)
```protobuf
syntax = "proto3";

package combined_manifold;

message Vector3D {
    double x = 1;
    double y = 2;
    double z = 3;
}

message VectorPayload {
    string vector_id = 1;
    Vector3D velocity_vector = 2;
    double throat_radius = 3;
    double magnetic_coupling = 4;
}

message SubstrateMetricsResponse {
    string status = 1;
    string version = 2;
    string mesh_status = 3;
    bool processing_stable = 4;
    uint64 execution_ticks = 5;
}

message IntentBand {
    string band_id = 1;
    double energy_delta = 2;
    double spin = 3;
    double temp = 4;
}

```
### 2.2 Telemetry Field Matrix
| Arc Registry | Parameter Name | Data Type | Boundary Restrictions / Valid Target Range | Definition & Core Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|---|
